00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Avarice can give strength to the weakest among us.

281
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Avarice?

282
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Avarice, Ashir?

283
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're saying this to me?

284
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Well, Monseigneur Ashir,

285
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If it had been avarice, Ashir, securing wealth was easy for me.

286
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Back when you were ready to die for me!

287
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You'd come with a marriage proposal --

288
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I was the one who had rejected it!

289
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The Lord alone can testify about my innocence.

290
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I have nothing else to say

291
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
In my defence.

292
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>O Lord! You know my predicament</i>

293
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>My life has become an affliction</i>

294
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Every gasp weighs at me</i>

295
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Why don't these doleful nights come to pass?</i>

296
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>How do I recount what has befallen me</i>

297
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Why is every last vestige of love immured?</i>

298
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Adan,

299
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Did you see your marks in physics and accountancy?

300
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes, I did.

301
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Adan, I'm serious.

302
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And why are your marks in Urdu so low?

303
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
My dear,

304
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't know what you'll do...

305
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And I don't know why you're so worried.

306
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd become a great businessman one day, Mum,

307
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And take care of everything.

308
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You'd become a great businessman,

309
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And take care of everything?

310
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
All without a degree?

311
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Those who have their own business don't need a degree, Mum.

312
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Now, it's not as if I have to apply to a company for a job.

313
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Adan, I'm serious!

314
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm in no mood for jokes.

315
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm very worried to see this report card.

316
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
There, now, Mum. Don't get so worried...

317
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I had no worries about Ashir's studies.

318
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He'd study on his own.

319
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
My dear,

320
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
This business and I --

321
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who knows what tomorrow may hold?

322
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What'd you do?

323
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't say that, Mum...

324
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Alright, I promise I'll concentrate on my studies and score good marks.

325
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't make false promises to me.

326
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Alright, if I scored good marks, what'd be my reward?

327
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Whatever you want.

328
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
In that case, I'd ask for something really big.

329
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd give you

330
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Whatever you ask for.

331
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Then,

332
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Start a company in my name

333
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just like you've started one in Ashir's name.

334
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
All its profit would be mine.

335
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Done.

336
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Alright,

337
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You can get whichever tutor you want to teach me.

338
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>My Lord...</i>

339
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Avarice?

340
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Avarice, Ashir?

341
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're saying this to me?

342
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Well, Monseigneur Ashir,

343
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If it had been avarice, Ashir, securing wealth was easy for me.

344
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Back when you were ready to die for me!

345
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You'd come with a marriage proposal --

346
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I was the one who had rejected it!

347
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The Lord alone can testify about my innocence.

348
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I have nothing else to say

349
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
In my defence.

350
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Rubina, get me my breakfast quick, I'll be opening the shop late.

351
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm coming...

352
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Can't you wait?

353
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Getting late...

354
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As if you'd earn

355
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Any good dough running that shop.

356
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Whatever,

357
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's currently my only source of income.

358
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just think

359
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How we'd run the household

360
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If I closed the shop.

361
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We were about to strike a great deal about that shop.

362
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What was wrong with us investing a few bucks in the business with Dad?

363
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It would've benefited you, of all the people.

364
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But your Mum's

365
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Almost seized control of it, and won't even let us talk about this.

366
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank goodness

367
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That Dad had this house transferred over to me in the marriage contract.

368
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who knows, your Mum

369
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
May have thrown me out of here.

370
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No, it's nothing like that.

371
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum's not bad at heart.

372
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It was at her insistence that Dad had transferred this house over to you.

373
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Then, why is she adamant about the shop?

374
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You don't exactly have a loving relationship with her either...

375
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As if she showers her affection on me!

376
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Whatever, Rubina,

377
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's my Mum.

378
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You'd have to live with her on cordial terms.

379
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You'll see,

380
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She'll agree about the shop, too.

381
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Fair enough.

382
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll try that, too.

383
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I know Aunt very well.

384
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She won't even agree if I took care of her.

